Wraps a token with the given parameters. Given interactions will call a method that creates the ontology of the token so the other methods (eg. lock, unlock, mint, burn, assign) can interact with the token. This interactions should be given by the bridge and be througly tested and checked before being used, as they can be used to call any function in the token contract.
